AGI - The Prince and Princess of Wales shared a photo never published before, to celebrate their 13th wedding anniversary. The new photo was posted on X and shows the couple after the wedding in 2011. Photographer Millie Pilkington commented: "Good wedding anniversary! I can't believe it's been 13 years. I remember this moment so well. I send you so much love on this special day."
<div </div
&nbsp;
Kate is immortalized in her iconic wedding dress - created by Sarah Burton for Alexander McQueen - while William wears the Irish Guard uniform. The couple married in Westminster Abbey on 29 April 2011 and had their first son, Prince George, in July 2013. It was a difficult start of year for the couple, with Kate and King Charles III, father of William, both in treatment for cancer. The Princess of Wales revealed her health conditions last month after speculation about why she hadn't been seen in public.&nbsp;
