The watch, with the initials JJA, belonged to the American businessman John Jacob Astor, who was 47 years old when the Titanic sank in the early hours of April 15, 1912. Astor, considered at the time one of the richest men in the world, with a heritage of 87 million dollars, equal to several billion today, died on the ship after helping his wife Madeleine to climb a lifeboat. Astor's body was found a week after the disaster, with the 14-carat gold pocket watch among his personal effects.&nbsp;
